heroku

- download heroku cli
    brew tap heroku/brew && brew install heroku

- login to use the cli
    heroku login

- create a new project
    heroku create <project-name>

- add a postgresql database
    heroku addons:create heroku-postgresql:hobby-dev --app <project-name>

- make a requirements.txt file
    pip freeze > requirements.txt

- create a Procfile and add app name
    echo "web: gunicorn app:<app-name>" > Procfile

- create a runtime.txt file to say python verison
    echo "python-3.9.8" > runtime.txt

- next step: git init, git add ., and git commit

- initialize repo to remote heroku repo
    heroku git:remote -a <project-name>

- push to remote repo
    git push heroku master

- run python shell on heroku server
    heroku run python

- login to remote db
    heroku pg:psql --app <project-name>